  "text": "The CNI (Container Network Interface) integration in Kubernetes involves a coordinated call chain across multiple components. The workflow begins with pod synchronization in pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_manager.go via the SyncPod function, which orchestrates the entire pod creation process.\n\nWhen a pod needs to be scheduled, the network plugin invocation happens through pod sandbox creation. In pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_sandbox.go, the createPodSandbox function calls generatePodSandboxConfig to prepare network configuration including port mappings, DNS settings, and hostname. The generatePodSandboxLinuxConfig function adds Linux-specific network configuration.\n\nThe actual CNI plugin invocation occurs through the Container Runtime Interface (CRI). In pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/instrumented_services.go, the RunPodSandbox function wraps the CRI call to create a pod sandbox. This delegates to the container runtime (containerd, CRI-O, etc.) which then invokes the CNI plugin to set up the network namespace and assign IP addresses.\n\nAfter sandbox creation, the network namespace is established by the CNI plugin, and IP address assignment happens through the IPAM (IP Address Management) plugin. The determinePodSandboxIPs function in pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_sandbox.go extracts the assigned IP addresses from the CRI response, which came from the CNI plugin's IPAM call.\n\nThe pod network status is managed through GetPodStatus in kuberuntime_manager.go, which retrieves network information from the pod sandbox status reported by the CRI runtime.\n\nAt the node level, IP address management is coordinated by the Node IPAM Controller in pkg/controller/nodeipam/node_ipam_controller.go. This controller allocates CIDR blocks to nodes, which are then sent to the kubelet. The updatePodCIDR function in pkg/kubelet/kubelet_network.go sends the pod CIDR to the runtime via UpdatePodCIDR in kuberuntime_manager.go. The CIDR allocation uses pkg/controller/nodeipam/ipam/cidr_allocator.go and pkg/controller/nodeipam/ipam/range_allocator.go for CIDR range management.\n\nNetwork plugin coordination is defined by the Runtime interface in pkg/kubelet/container/runtime.go, which specifies methods for UpdatePodCIDR and other network-related operations. The sync result tracking in pkg/kubelet/container/sync_result.go includes SetupNetwork action to track network setup failures.\n\nAdditional network configuration is handled in pkg/kubelet/kubelet_pods.go for pod-specific network settings, and pkg/kubelet/kubelet_network_linux.go manages Linux-specific network utilities like iptables firewall rules."
}

